.TH ET 1 "2026-02-19" "et" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
et \- log task start messages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B et
.RI [ TASK ... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B et
emits a task start message in the form:
.PP
TASK START: <task>...
.PP
Task text is resolved in this order:
.IP "1." 4
Join positional arguments with spaces.
.IP "2." 4
Use the
.B TASK
environment variable if no positional arguments are provided.
.PP
If
.B loggerx
is available in PATH,
.B et
calls:
.PP
loggerx INFO "TASK START: <task>..."
.PP
If
.B loggerx
is not available,
.B et
prints a plain UTC INFO line to stdout.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h , " --help"
Show help and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.B et "Refactor parser"
.PP
.B TASK="Prepare release" et
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 2
Invalid input (for example, empty task).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR loggerx (1)
